<subSubSection id="90163565B617D9E6F43B98B52F1154C9" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="new records">
<paragraph id="3B9575975559EC7823C0073AE085F333" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">New records.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="74A7D9B0567A262FD2D9D9A06E252D3F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Israel • 2 spcms; Ashqelon; 
<geoCoordinate id="6483CB22D2D83F75BE18ACBF7B28D035" degrees="31.6891" direction="north" orientation="latitude" precision="5" value="31.6891">31.6891°N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="A65001DADA21497C0E8E4A1FF977EEA0" degrees="34.5257" direction="east" orientation="longitude" precision="5" value="34.5257">34.5257°E</geoCoordinate>
; depth 28 m; 31 Oct 2018; offshore rocky reef; suction sampler; HELM project (sample S59_2F) • 1 spcm; west of Rosh HaNikra Islands; 
<geoCoordinate id="5D52762773EC18D9268B0BAD5274055E" degrees="33.0704" direction="north" orientation="latitude" precision="5" value="33.0704">33.0704°N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="C559F6587E1B0E43126ED1117F183E16" degrees="35.0926" direction="east" orientation="longitude" precision="5" value="35.0926">35.0926°E</geoCoordinate>
; depth 12 m; 1 May 2018; rocky substrate; suction sampler; HELM project (sample S14_4F) • 5 spcms; same collecting data as for preceding; 29 Oct. 2018; HELM project (samples S52_1F, S52_2F).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6CB69F6EE461EBE98982B0858049FFFF" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="E4C5D3E5632DD87DB7650DD96BE9CF79" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CABE70F62F5DF17E646605BD83119033" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Until now, the first record of this species from the Mediterranean was considered to be by 
<normalizedToken id="E9217D3684E71647D310CB9B40C1B98F" originalValue="Öztürk">Oeztuerk</normalizedToken>
and van Aartsen (2006), who reported on material obtained from shallow-water sediment samples collected along the Turkish Levantine (Viransehir, Mersin Bay) and Aegean coasts (
<normalizedToken id="98BA63307D15E62EF9B4277B3E14367C" originalValue="Güllük">Guelluek</normalizedToken>
Bay) in 1997 and 2000, respectively. However, already 
<bibRefCitation id="7B30C608A2E8DD1A48344787DD050B5F" author="van der Linden, J" journalOrPublisher="Basteria" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="3 - 63" refId="B130" refString="van der Linden, J, Eikenboom, JCA, 1992. On the taxonomy of the Recent species of the genus Chrysallida Carpenter from Europe, the Canary Islands and the Azores (Gastropoda, Pyramidellidae). Basteria 56: 3 - 63" title="On the taxonomy of the Recent species of the genus Chrysallida Carpenter from Europe, the Canary Islands and the Azores (Gastropoda, Pyramidellidae)." volume="56" year="1992">van der Linden and Eikenboom (1992)</bibRefCitation>
described and illustrated 
<taxonomicName id="6BE924D6F07685201BF86521B6BC9162" class="Gastropoda" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. nana" order="Sacoglossa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="nana">
<emphasis id="D9F8CF48E5EC35009E9C4A7C32A68353" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. nana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Levantine Sea (page 60, Figure 
<figureCitation id="432F46BBC569FFD7AE3C150DF359A18D" captionStart="Figure 41" captionStartId="F41" captionText="Figure 41. Scintilla cf. violescens Kuroda &amp; Taki, 1961, Haifa, Israel: right (A) and left (B) valve outer views, left (C) and right (D) valve inner views, hinge of left (E, G) and right (F, H) valve. Scale bars: 2 mm (A-D); 0.5 mm (E-H)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1010.58759.figure41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/496994" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">41</figureCitation>
), referring to it as 
<taxonomicName id="ECBDF2F46FEC1484E46A67965DEE32FD" class="Gastropoda" family="Pyramidellidae" genus="Chrysallida" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chrysallida" order="Heterostropha" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="003838FE95C852645E592698B2C2E8FA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Chrysallida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spec. C in the lack of a species-level identification. Their material consisted of a single individual, likely an empty shell, but not specified by the authors, from Mersin (south-eastern Turkey) with unknown collecting date, housed in the collection of J. van der Linden (The Hague, The Netherlands). Although we were unable to examine this material, the excellent and detailed line drawing provided enabled an unambiguous assignment of 
<taxonomicName id="8DD8B9C179BBE6339A1C835036242B90" class="Gastropoda" family="Pyramidellidae" genus="Chrysallida" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chrysallida" order="Heterostropha" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="41FCF05BA06C44C92BFD202611BA55B5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Chrysallida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spec. C to 
<taxonomicName id="4F9252BD8A907C430C522CD798391C72" class="Gastropoda" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. nana" order="Sacoglossa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="nana">
<emphasis id="82C266628DC742A7CF2FBF63D562B7D3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. nana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; thus, 
<bibRefCitation id="A0A9562D0306AA4A0FCBC81793B5AD0F" author="van der Linden, J" journalOrPublisher="Basteria" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="3 - 63" refId="B130" refString="van der Linden, J, Eikenboom, JCA, 1992. On the taxonomy of the Recent species of the genus Chrysallida Carpenter from Europe, the Canary Islands and the Azores (Gastropoda, Pyramidellidae). Basteria 56: 3 - 63" title="On the taxonomy of the Recent species of the genus Chrysallida Carpenter from Europe, the Canary Islands and the Azores (Gastropoda, Pyramidellidae)." volume="56" year="1992">van der Linden and Eikenboom (1992)</bibRefCitation>
should be regarded the first Mediterranean record. Today, the known Mediterranean distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="9EFC07ADD740D88AA42991CAF719AFB0" class="Gastropoda" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. nana" order="Sacoglossa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="nana">
<emphasis id="77822C7AC648AF9199EFC777F8D9FFFA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. nana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
includes Turkey, Lebanon, and Israel (
<bibRefCitation id="3783392C72C05AB848311AC27EA98502" author="Bogi, C" journalOrPublisher="La Conchiglia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B38" refString="Bogi, C, Galil, BS, 2006. Nuovi ritrovamenti lungo le coste israeliane. Notiziario S.I.M.24: 16-18." title="Nuovi ritrovamenti lungo le coste israeliane. Notiziario S. I. M. 24: 16 - 18." year="2006">Bogi and Galil 2006</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="A73CE06F20B01E9088A4B2D9169D0E2A" author="Giannuzzi-Savelli, R" journalOrPublisher="Biological Invasions" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B90" refString="Giannuzzi-Savelli, R, Pusateri, F, Micali, P, Nofroni, I, Bartolini, S, 2014. Atlante delle conchiglie marine del Mediterraneo Vol. 5 (Heterobranchia). Edizioni Danaus, Palermo, 111 + 191 pp." title="Atlante delle conchiglie marine del Mediterraneo Vol. 5 (Heterobranchia). Edizioni Danaus, Palermo, 111 + 191 pp." year="2014">Giannuzzi-Savelli et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
). To our knowledge, this is the first record of living individuals of 
<taxonomicName id="DAED6E024150DCA81DA0FD81F31957F6" class="Gastropoda" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. nana" order="Sacoglossa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="nana">
<emphasis id="4614957DDCD8CD6435266613507F7870" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. nana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Israel; here, the species occurs along both the southern (Ashqelon) and northern coasts (west of Rosh HaNikra Islands) on rocky bottoms at 12-28 m depth.
</paragraph>
